theme_override_styles/normal = SubResource("StyleBoxFlat_nrcq3")
text = "[b]Corner curvature[/b]"

[node name="Content" parent="HBoxContainer/CurvatureTabButton/Tooltip" index="1"]
theme_override_styles/normal = SubResource("StyleBoxFlat_rx5ek")
text = "Edit the curvature of each corner. Represents the value of a superellipse function 
which gives different curve shapes. Positive numbers makes corner shapes curved 
outward which get closer to a square corner as the value gets higher, negative values 
makes corner shapes curved inward, they are the exact inverse of their positive values.

Click on the corner icon to select a preset.

[b]Round:[/b] Default value, makes a normal circle.

[b]Squircle:[/b] Intermediate shape between a square and a circle. Needs a higher
corner radius to visually compensate comparated to a round corner.

[b]Bevel:[/b] Makes the corner a straight line, it acts the same as if [i]corner_detail[/i]
value were 1.

[b]Scoop:[/b] The inverse of a round corner.

[b]Reverse squircle:[/b] The inverse of a squircle corner.

[b]Notch:[/b] Makes a square cut inside the corner."

